1 elec tion shall be held on the same day as the Presidential
2 Preferential Primary and on the fourth Tuesday of August in each
3 even-numbered year.
4 3. If only two candidates qualify to have their names appear on
5 the ballot, the names of both candidates shall appear on the ballot
6 at the board of education general election.
7 4. If more than two candidates qualify to have their names
8 appear on the ballot, the names of all such candidates shall appear
9 on the ballot at the board of education primary election. A
10 candidate receiving more than fifty percent (50%) of the votes cast
11 in the board of education primary election shall be elected to the
12 office. If no candidate receives more than fifty percent (50%) of
13 the votes cast in the board of education primary election, then the
14 two candidates with the highest number of votes shall appear on the
15 ballot at the board of education general election.
16 B. Elections on the question of making a levy or levies for
17 schools under Section 9, Section 9B or Section 10 of Article X of
18 the Oklahoma Constitution shall be held on the second Tuesday in
19 February of each year, except in any year when a Presidential
20 Preferential Primary is held in February, then the election shall be
21 held on the same day as the Presidential Preferential Primary.
22 C. The board of education of every school district or
23 technology center school district may call a special election for
24 the purpose of voting on any matter or question authorized by law.
